==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Conglutinant
<hw>Con*glu"ti*nant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.,
<ets>conglutinans</ets>, p. pr.]</ety> <def>Cementing together; uniting
closely; causing to adhere; promoting healing, as of a wound or a broken
bone, by adhesion of the parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conglutinate</ent>⟦br⟧
